&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Octus&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Octus is a leading global provider of credit intelligence, data, and analytics. Since 2013, tens of thousands of professionals across hedge fund, investment banking, management consulting, and law firm verticals have come to rely on Octus to make better, faster, and more confident decisions in pace with the fast-moving credit markets. &lt;br&gt;For more information, visit: https://octus.com/&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working at Octus&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Octus hires growth-minded innovators and trailblazers across the globe to drive our business and culture. Our core values – Action Oriented, Customer First Mindset, Effective Team Players, and Driven to Excel – define an organizational ethos that’s as high-performing as it is human. Among other perks, Octus employees enjoy competitive health benefits, matched 401k and pension plans, PTO, generous parental leave, gym subsidies, educational reimbursements for career development, recognition programs, pet-friendly offices (US only), and much more.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Octus is looking for an Account Management Associate to join our growing commercial team in London. This is an ideal opportunity for someone eager to build a career in account management and revenue generation, as you&#39;ll build the commercial skills that lead to a full Account Manager position. Working closely with our Head of EMEA Account Management, you will own a book of autorenewal clients, developing your expertise in retention, relationship management, and identifying growth opportunities across our EMEA client base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This full-time position is located in our London office on a hybrid (3 days in office per week) working model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the day-to-day management and support of a defined book of EMEA clients on autorenewal contracts, serving as their primary point of contact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle client questions and queries promptly, including those related to services, user access, training and content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain regular client contact touchpoints and proactively schedule outreach to keep relationships active&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think commercially about each client relationship, identifying and flagging potential cross-sell opportunities to the broader Account Management and Sales teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive high client retention across the book, working to minimise cancellations and resolve at-risk situations early&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with Sales, Customer Success, Marketing and Commercial Operations to ensure seamless client service and consistent process adherence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relay client feedback on product and platform experience to the product team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ideal for a graduate or someone with 1-2 years of experience, with a strong desire to move into a revenue-generating Account Management role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated interest in financial markets, credit or leveraged finance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organised and detail-oriented, with the ability to manage multiple accounts and workstreams simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in French or German is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative team player who thrives in a fast-paced, high-growth environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Octus values&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actio

