&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for candidates who have experience managing relationships with and selling to the buyside, banks, or both.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage all aspects of the renewal cycle for Octus’ subscription relationships covering a book of either banking or buyside accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage key client interactions with a focus on expansion opportunities within accounts and subscription renewals targeting 115%+ net retention&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a strong knowledge of your client base in order to identify and close cross sell opportunities, which is fundamental to achieving your quota&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with customer success to deliver excellent client service and customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with Octus’ product team to identify opportunities for product and platform enhancements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and analyze KPIs and product usage on accounts to determine appropriate relationship management strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5+ years of progressive experience in an account management role selling to buyside firms or banks, preferably with experience working in credit.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage complex institutions involving multiple teams and stakeholders.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to develop a deep knowledge of a complex suite of products (such as datasets, API feeds and research). Proven success in hitting quota and executing on cross-sell opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organized, detail-oriented with the ability to prioritize and respond quickly; ability to keep on top of all requirements with multiple ongoing workstreams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal, verbal and written communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Salesforce required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a hybrid schedule (3 days in office per week)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equal Employment Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
