&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working at Octus&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Octus hires growth-minded innovators and trailblazers across the globe to drive our business and culture. Our core values – Action Oriented, Customer First Mindset, Effective Team Players, and Driven to Excel – define an organizational ethos that’s as high-performing as it is human. Among other perks, Octus employees enjoy competitive health benefits, matched 401k and pension plans, PTO, generous parental leave, gym subsidies, educational reimbursements for career development, recognition programs, pet-friendly offices (US only), and much more.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced credit analyst as Head of Credit Research to lead our European leveraged finance research, with a focus on high yield performing and distressed credit coverage. This senior leader will be responsible for a third of Octus’ trifecta, meaning the leader will work closely with senior lawyers and reporters with cross border experience and expertise, to create our best-in-class research and analysis. The head of credit research will manage a team of nine analysts, shaping research coverage, establishing best practices and KPIs, and driving collaboration across the Editorial department and with commercial and marketing teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Head of Credit Research will be a driving force in originating actionable investment ideas for our clients so they can stay ahead of the curve. The successful candidate will oversee the publication of timely and insightful credit research reports in touch with market trends. The role requires expertise in fundamental credit analysis, relative value, valuation, and restructuring as well as a proven ability to innovate and deliver value to our subscribers. You will play a key role in developing and mentoring junior talent, ensuring high analytical standards, and improving time to market for research outputs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly visible, client-facing role, offering exposure to top institutional asset managers, hedge funds, investment banks, trading desks, and financial and legal advisors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will be expected to have a combination of the following:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;track record of successful investment ideas,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;deal making (from pitch to execution),&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;an existing network in the credit market,&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ability to convey a clear pitch in writing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;experience in team leadership (hiring, training, managing skills, managing career development)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Senior leadership role in a fast-growing, collaborative research environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to shape best-in-class credit research and coverage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous benefits package&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hybrid remote work flexibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Progression opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
